# CitreaTestnet Configuration Example

# Basic RPC Configuration (Required)
CITREA_TESTNET_WALLET_ADDRESS=0x...
CITREA_TESTNET_WALLET_PRIVATE_KEY=...
CITREA_TESTNET_GATEWAY_URL=https://rpc.testnet.citrea.xyz
# CITREA_TESTNET_API_KEY= # Not needed for public RPC
CITREA_TESTNET_CHAIN_ID=5115

# Goldsky Integration (Optional - for transaction history)
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT: Requires a deployed subgraph to function!
# 
# To enable transaction history:
# 1. Create a Goldsky account at https://goldsky.com
# 2. Create and deploy a subgraph with transfer entities:
#    ```bash
#    goldsky subgraph deploy citrea-transfers/1.0.0 \
#      --from-abi ./citrea-abi.json \
#      --chain citrea-testnet
#    ```
# 3. Verify the subgraph schema includes 'transfers' and 'tokenTransfers' entities
# 4. Set the endpoint URL below
# 
# Format: https://api.goldsky.com/api/public/<project_id>/subgraphs/<name>/<version>/gn
# Example:
# CITREA_TESTNET_GOLDSKY_SUBGRAPH_URL=https://api.goldsky.com/api/public/project_xyz/subgraphs/citrea-transfers/1.0.0/gn

# Without deployed subgraph: Transaction history will ALWAYS return empty arrays
# With deployed subgraph: Transaction history available via GraphQL queries
# 
# NOTE: The subgraph schema must match the expected entity structure in goldsky.service.ts